{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pancreatitis-acute/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"4a71e62c-d161-5d2b-b926-25de6682b65d","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 450432c6-57c2-4973-8067-0e3a74afbbe7 --><h2>How common is acute pancreatitis?</h2><!-- end field 450432c6-57c2-4973-8067-0e3a74afbbe7 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 48131bfa-d879-4366-89c1-8ff3ec11282f --><!-- begin field 5335aa76-5fcc-4814-98f8-39edb8a90a45 --><ul><li>The reported worldwide annual incidence of acute pancreatitis is 13–45 cases per 100,000 people [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pancreatitis-acute/references/\">Working Group IAP/APA Acute Pancreatitis Guidelines, 2013</a>]. </li><li>In the UK, most hospitals serving a population of 300,000–400,000 people will admit approximately 100 people with acute pancreatitis per year [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pancreatitis-acute/references/\">Johnson, 2014</a>].</li><li>Most people (80%) with acute pancreatitis will have mild acute pancreatitis. The remainder will have moderately severe or severe acute pancreatitis [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pancreatitis-acute/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2015</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 5335aa76-5fcc-4814-98f8-39edb8a90a45 --><!-- end item 48131bfa-d879-4366-89c1-8ff3ec11282f -->","topic":{"id":"a1189e29-6f67-5025-b150-794cebf1fefb","topicId":"dd099a94-8039-4337-a80f-f1f38b3dd527","topicName":"Pancreatitis - acute","slug":"pancreatitis-acute","lastRevised":"Last revised in May 2016","chapters":[{"id":"d870d218-25f0-5c41-905f-a5aa76957a7a","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"43d71289-ccc5-5801-a291-bc4293cb7be7","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got